    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "\nPatients affected by virus influenza A(H1N1) and displaying multi-organ failure (respiratory, renal, hemodynamic, hepatic) should be admitted to the ICU.Most patients with pulmonary infiltrates and ARF should undergo mechanical ventilation in an ICU, with the option of round-the-clock invasive or noninvasive assisted ventilation.Invasive mechanical ventilation is \u201cthe gold standard\u201d for treating ARF.Early application of NIV can be recommended for young patients with organ failure as measured by the SOFA scale where hypoxemic ARF is the main problem.\n",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Key Recommendations ::: Introduction",
            "ref_spans": []
        }
    ],
